bug.short_desc: rd.dasd= not appended on the kernel command line after installation
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: After installation on s390x using DASD disks, the rd.dasd= parameter is not appended to the kernel command line. Because of that, no DASD disks are visible during boot and booting fails.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): anaconda-25.20.1-1.fc25 python3-blivet-2.1.2-1.fc25
How reproducible: always
Steps to Reproduce: 1. run manual installation in text mode on s390x 2. use all DASD devices, continue with the default options 3. reboot when the installation is done
Actual results: system fails to boot, DASD devices are not brought online
Expected results: rd.dasd= on the kernel command line on installed system

Created attachment 1203759 zipl.conf
/etc/zipl.conf from installed system
Can't reproduce the issue in VNC install with fix for bug 1378338 applied on top of F-25 Beta RC (http://s390.koji.fedoraproject.org/compose/25/Fedora-25-20161007.0/).
I can confirm it's not reproducible any more on compose Fedora-25-20161007.0 (F-25 Beta RC) with updates image from http://fedora.danny.cz/s390/updates-1378338.img (bug 1378338). I'm closing the bug.
